The Washington Post's investigation revealed wounded soldiers left forgotten at Walter Reed due to bureaucratic failures.
President George W. Bush's commitment to veterans was emphasized amid calls for improved care standards.
The Defense Department vowed to address neglect in military hospitals, with proposed legislation to streamline services.
Defense Secretary Robert Gates expressed dismay over the disgraceful treatment reported, promising accountability.
